-- Canada Court Says CRTC Doesn’t Have Television Fee Power
-- B y   T h e o p h i l o s   A r g i t i s
-- 2012-12-13T14:53:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-13/canada-court-says-crtc-doesn-t-have-television-fee-authority.html
 Canada’s Supreme Court ruled the
country’s broadcast regulator doesn’t have the authority to
require cable and satellite companies to pay television
networks for the right to carry their local signals.  The court made the ruling in a decision released today in
Ottawa.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Theophilos Argitis in Ottawa at 
 targitis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
